Lien 25 12.4 Remedies Cumulative 25 12.5 Waiver of Partition 25 12.6 Limitation of Liability 26 ARTICLE 13 WAIVER OF JURY TRIAL 26 13.1 Waiver of Jury Trial 26 ARTICLE 14 NOTICES 26 14.1 Notices 26 ARTICLE 15 MISCELLANEOUS PROVISIONS 27 15.1 Transfers 27 15.2 Right to Encumber 27 15.3 Pledge, Collateral Assignment or Encumbrance 28 15.4 Expenses 28 15.5 Reservation of Rights 28 15.6 Governing Law 28 15.7 Compliance with Laws 29 15.8 Survival 29 15.9 Further Assurances 29 15.10 Non-Recourse 29 15.11 Successors and Assigns 29 15.12 Entire Agreement 29 15.13 Amendment 30 15.14 Waiver 30 15.15 Validity 30 15.16 Benefit and Binding Effect 30 15.17 Time of Essence 30 15.18 Counterparts 31 INDEX OF EXHIBITS Exhibit A Shared Facilities Exhibit B Percentage Interest of Owners Exhibit C Insurance Requirements Exhibit D Ground Lease SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT THIS SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this "Agreement") is entered into as of July 14, 2020 (the "Effective Date") BY AND BETWEEN: EGP SOLAR 1, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company, ("EGP"), and MISSISSQUOI, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company, ("MA"), Each of EGP and MA are referred to herein individually as a "Party," and collectively "Parties" RECITALS: A. MA owns and operates a 24 MW rated capacity hydro generation facility located in Sheldon Springs Vermont that consists of generators, turbines, meters, and associated collection and interconnection lines and related facilities and improvements (the "MA Project"). B. EGP owns and operates a 2.4 MW solar generation facility on leased land of the MA Project (the "EGP Project"). C. MA owns, operates, and maintains a 46 kV substation, interconnection line and other associated facilities, including a switchyard, breakers, substation, SCADA and metering, connecting the MA Project to the transmission system and balancing authority area controlled by NE-ISO and owned by VELCO, all more particularly described in Exhibit A as those Shared Facilities in respect of which MA is identified as the Owner/Lessor (the "Shared Facilities"). As of the Effective Date, MA owns one hundred percent (100%) of the interests in the MA Shared Facilities. D. MA owns or leases approximately 494 acres of land which includes the parcels more particularly described in in that certain Amended and Restated Ground Lease dated as of January 22, 2020 and attached hereto as Exhibit D (the "Ground Lease") granting EGP certain rights and interests to those parcels ("Shared Parcels"). E. MA desires to lease to EGP the Shared Facilities, as more particularly described herein, for the use, operation, access, construction, alteration, and maintenance of the EGP Project. F. The Owners wish to set forth herein their respective rights and obligations regarding such lease rights, joint use, maintenance, repair, replacement of, and alterations to the Shared Facilities. AGREEMENT: NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants contained in this Agreement and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is acknowledged, the Parties agree as follows: Article 1 DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATION 1.1 Definitions Unless otherwise noted, capitalized terms not defined in the body of this Agreement have the following meanings. (a) "Affiliate" means with respect to any Person, any other Person that directly or indirectly Controls, is Controlled by or is under common Control with, the first mentioned Person. (b) "Agreement" has the meaning set forth in the preamble above. (c) "Business Day" means any day other than Saturday, Sunday or any federal holiday. (d) "Capacity Interest" means, in respect of each Owner, the percentage of the aggregate capacity (in megawatts) of all of the Projects that is represented by such Owner's Project. (e) "Casualty Event" means an event that causes all or a portion of the Shared Facilities to be damaged, destroyed or rendered unfit for normal use for any reason whatsoever. (f) "Condemnation Event" means any compulsory transfer or taking or transfer under threat of compulsory transfer or taking of all or a material part of the Shared Facilities by any Governmental Authority or entity acting under power of eminent domain. (g) "Confidential Information", with respect to a given Disclosing Party and the respective Receiving Party, means, collectively and individually, all data, materials and information (including software, data, technology, know-how, trade secrets, processes, ideas, inventions (whether patentable or not), prototypes, schematics, design plans, drawings, pricing information, customer and service provider lists, business arrangements, business information, financial information, financial results, technical information, analyses, forecasts, compilations, studies, contracts, agreements, and planning or strategy information) provided by or on behalf of a Party (each Party in such capacity, a "Disclosing Party") to the other Party (each Party in such capacity, a "Receiving Party") or the Receiving Party's Representatives, or to which the Receiving Party or the Receiving Party's Representatives are given access by or on behalf of the Disclosing Party, whether verbally or in written or electronic form, related to the Disclosing Party, any Project, the Shared Facilities, or the Parties in connection with this Agreement. Notwithstanding the foregoing, Confidential Information under this Agreement does not include any information that: (a) is now publicly available, or that later becomes publicly available through no action by the Receiving Party or the Receiving Party's Representatives in violation of this Agreement; (b) is already in the possession of the Receiving Party or the Receiving Party's Representatives and is not, to Receiving Party's knowledge, subject to a confidentiality or fiduciary obligation at the time of the information's disclosure under this Agreement; (c) is lawfully received from any source other than the Disclosing Party or the Disclosing Party's Representatives under circumstances not involving, to the Receiving Party's knowledge, a breach of any fiduciary or confidentiality obligation; or (d) is independently developed by or for the Receiving Party or the Receiving Party's Representatives without reference to, or the use of, any portion of the Confidential Information. (h) "Control" means, with respect to any Person, the power to direct the management or policies of such Person, directly or indirectly, whether through the ownership of shares or other securities therein, by contract or otherwise, provided that the direct or indirect ownership in that Person by any other Person and/or by any other Person not dealing at Arm's Length with such first mentioned Person of fifty percent (50%) or more of the share capital or other equity interests of the first mentioned Person possessing the power to vote in the election of directors, managers or other Persons performing similar functions shall be deemed to constitute Control of that first mentioned Person and the words "Controlled by", "Controlling" and similar words have corresponding meanings; (i) "Default Rate" means a rate per annum equal to the lesser of (a) a varying rate per annum equal to the sum of (i) LIBOR or if LIBOR is no longer being published a similar rate reasonably agreed to by the Parties, plus (ii) three percent per annum, and (b) the maximum rate permitted by Law. (j) "Disclosing Party" has the meaning set forth in the definition of "Confidential Information." (k) "Dispute" means any controversy, claim or dispute that arises out of or in connection with this Agreement or the construction, interpretation, performance, breach, termination, enforceability or validity of this Agreement, whether the same is based on rights, privileges or interests recognized by or based upon statute, contract, agreement (whether written or oral), tort, common law or other Law. (l) "Effective Date" has the meaning set forth in the preamble above. (m) "Emergency" means any occurrence, in the reasonable judgment of a Party, that may arise that requires immediate action and which constitutes a serious actual or potential hazard to the safety of Persons or property or that may materially interfere with the safe, economical or environmentally sound operation of the Shared Facilities or any Project. (n) "Environmental Laws" means all Laws, whenever enacted or in effect, concerning pollution, protection of human health, safety or the environment or preservation or reclamation of natural resources (including endangered or threatened species),or relating to the use, storage, disposal, generation and transportation of Hazardous Substances or imposing liability for injury to human health, property or the environment. (o) "Event of Default" has the meaning set forth in Section 12.1. (p) "Financing Party" means any Person providing direct or indirect debt or equity financing, refinancing or extending credit (including any financing lease) to an Owner. (q) "Force Majeure" means acts of God or any other casualty or occurrence, condition, event or circumstance of any kind or nature not reasonably within the affected Party's control and which could not have been avoided by reasonable measures or foreseeable by the affected Party, including strikes, slow-downs or labor difficulties, fires, flood, earthquakes, explosions, natural disasters, or other hazards, acts of public enemies, riots, civil commotions, insurrection, or war. Force Majeure expressly does not include: any delay in performing or failure of performance of any contractual provision by a Party (except to the extent caused by a Force Majeure event); late delivery or breakage of equipment or materials (except to the extent caused by a Force Majeure event); or economic hardship. (r) "GAAP" has the meaning set forth in Section 1.6. (s) "Governmental Approval" means any permit, license, certificate, concession, approval, consent, ratification, permission, clearance, confirmation, exemption, waiver, franchise, certification, designation, rating, registration, variance, qualification, accreditation or authorization issued, granted, given or otherwise made available by or under the authority of any Governmental Authority or pursuant to any Law. (t) "Governmental Authority" means any domestic government, whether federal, local, regional, municipal or other political jurisdiction, and any agency or authority, instrumentality, court, tribunal, board, commission, bureau, arbitrator, arbitration tribunal or other tribunal, or any quasi-governmental or other entity, including, but not limited to, any ISO, RTO and reliability council, insofar as it exercises a legislative, judicial, regulatory, administrative, expropriation or taxing power or function of or pertaining to government. (u) "Hazardous Substances" means: (a) any hazardous materials, hazardous wastes, hazardous substances, toxic wastes, solid wastes, and toxic substances as those or similar terms are defined under any Environmental Laws; (b) any asbestos or asbestos containing material; (c) polychlorinated biphenyls ("PCBs"), or PCB containing materials or fluids; (d) radon; (e) any petroleum, petroleum hydrocarbons, petroleum products, crude oil and any fractions or derivatives thereof; and (f) any other hazardous, radioactive, toxic or noxious substance, material, pollutant, or contaminant that, whether by its nature or its use, or exposure to is subject to regulation or could give rise to liability under any Environmental Laws. (v) "Indemnified Parties" has the meaning set forth in Section 9.1. (w) "Laws" means any applicable constitutional provisions, statutes, acts, codes, laws, rules, regulations, ordinances, orders, decrees, rulings, judgments or decisions of a Governmental Authority or arbitral body. (x) "Lease Interest" means the leasehold interest granted to the relevant Lessee pursuant to Article 3. (y) "Lessee" means, collectively, with respect to a particular Shared Facility, each Owner identified as lessee of such Shared Facility in Exhibit A. (z) "Lessor" means, with respect to a particular Shared Facility, the Owner identified as lessor such Shared Facility in Exhibit A. (aa) "Liabilities" means any and all claims, actions, debts, losses, liabilities, damages, expenses, awards, judgments, settlement payments, fines, penalties, costs, royalties, assessments (tax or otherwise), proceedings, deficiencies or obligations, whether civil or criminal, including those arising out of any investigation, action, claim, settlement, compromise, judgment or award, by any Person, of any nature, whether known or unknown, absolute, accrued, contingent or otherwise and whether due or to become due, and whether or not resulting from third party claims, and any out-of-pocket costs and expenses (including court costs and fees, reasonable legal counsels', accountants', or other fees and expenses) incurred in defending against or investigating any of the same. (bb) "Liens" means all mortgages, deeds of trust, liens, debentures, security interests, pledges, conditional sale contracts, proceedings, judgment liens, orders, rights of first refusal, charges and other encumbrances or restrictions of any kind, whether recorded or unrecorded. (cc) "Loss Event" means a Casualty Event or a Condemnation Event. (dd) "Owner(s)" means collectively or individually EGP and/or MA; (ee) "Ownership Interest" means the ownership interest retained by the relevant Party pursuant to Article 3. (ff) "Parties" and "Party" have the respective meanings set forth in the preamble above. (gg) "Percentage Interest" means the percentage as set forth on Exhibit B attached hereto with respect to Lessor and Lessee of each Shared Facility, which percentage is intended to reflect the respective proportion of each Shared Facility to be used and accessed by Lessor and Lessee pursuant to this Agreement. (hh) "Permitted Liens" means Liens in favor of financing parties; (ii) "Person" means an individual, corporation, partnership, Limited Liability Company, unincorporated association, unincorporated syndicate, unincorporated organization, Governmental Authority, trust, trustee, executor, administrator or other legal representative. (jj) "Project Site" means the real property on which the applicable Project is located. (kk) "Project Specific Assets" means, for each Project, any of the assets comprising such Project, the Project Site underlying such Project and the agreements and contractual arrangements related to such Project and Project Site. For the avoidance of doubt, the Project Specific Assets shall exclude any of the Shared Facilities. (ll) "Prudent Industry Practices" means those practices, standards, designs, methods, means, techniques, equipment and acts adopted by, engaged in or approved by a significant portion of hydro and solar energy industry in North America as good practices applicable to the operation and maintenance of solar, hydro, and electrical energy facilities, under conditions comparable to those applicable in respect of the Projects, or any of the practices, standards, designs, methods, means, techniques, equipment and acts which, in the exercise of skill, diligence, prudence, foresight and reasonable judgment in light of the facts known at the time the decision was made, could reasonably have been expected to accomplish the desired result at a reasonable cost consistent with good wind energy business practices, reliability, safety and expedition. (mm) "RTAC" means an industry standard Remote Terminal Unit used to capture and collect data. (nn) "Receiving Party" has the meaning set forth in the definition of "Confidential Information." (oo) "Removal Costs" means any costs, expenses or other Liabilities associated with the decommissioning or removal of the Shared Facilities upon the cessation of operations of the Projects. (pp) "Representatives" means, with respect to a Party, such Party's Affiliates, officers, directors, managers, members, shareholders, partners, employees, lenders (actual or prospective), investors (actual or prospective), transferees of the Ownership Interest or Lease Interest, as applicable (actual or prospective), purchasers (actual or prospective), contractors, vendors, suppliers, advisors, consultants, agents and representatives. (qq) "Required Consent" means a unanimous decision by the Owners. (rr) "Shared Expenses" means, in respect of each Shared Facility, all costs, expenses (including labor expenses) and other Liabilities arising under or relating to such Shared Facility but excluding any costs and expenses to restore or repair the Shared Facility arising from Lessor's or Lessee's actions or inactions in violation of this Agreement or a Governmental Approval; (ss) "Shared Facilities Representative" has the meaning set forth in Section 5.3. (tt) "Transfer" means to grant, sell, assign, set over, deliver, convey, demise, dispose of or otherwise transfer an interest in tangible or intangible assets. (uu) "Withdrawal Date" has the meaning set forth in Section 6.8(a). (vv) "Withdrawal Notice" has the meaning set forth in Section 6.8(a). 1.2 Sections and Headings The division of this Agreement into Sections and the insertion of headings and an index are for convenience of reference only and shall not affect the construction or interpretation of this Agreement. The terms "this Agreement", "hereof", "hereunder" and similar expressions refer to this Agreement and not to any particular Section or other portion hereof and include any agreement or instrument supplemental or ancillary hereto. Unless otherwise specified, any reference herein to an Article, Section, Subsection, Paragraph or Exhibit refers to the specified Article, Section, Subsection or Paragraph or, or Exhibit to, this Agreement. 1.3 Rules of Construction In this Agreement: (a) words importing the singular number only shall include the plural and vice versa and words importing the masculine gender only shall include the feminine and neuter genders and vice versa; (b) the words "include", "includes" and "including" mean "include", "includes" or "including", in each case, "without limitation"; (c) reference to any agreement or other instrument in writing means such agreement or other instrument in writing as amended, modified, replaced or supplemented from time to time; (d) unless otherwise indicated, time periods within which a payment is to be made or any other action is to be taken hereunder shall be calculated excluding the day on which the period commences and including the day on which the period ends; (e) whenever any payment to be made or action to be taken hereunder is required to be made or taken on a day other than a Business Day, such payment shall be made or action taken on the next following Business Day; and (f) any reference to a Party includes (i) any successor to such Party and (ii) any Person to whom such Party has assigned any of its rights hereunder in accordance with Section 15.1 but only in respect of those rights so assigned. 1.4 Currency Unless otherwise indicated, all dollar amounts referred to in this Agreement are expressed in United States Dollars. 1.5 No Waiver The failure of any Party to insist upon strict adherence to any provision of this Agreement on any occasion shall not be considered a waiver or deprive that Party of the right thereafter to insist upon strict adherence to such provision or any other provision of this Agreement. No purported waiver shall be effective as against any Party unless consent is provided in writing by such Party. The waiver by any Party of a breach of any provision of this Agreement shall not operate or be construed as a waiver of any subsequent or other breach. 1.6 Accounting Terms In this Agreement, accounting terms that are not defined herein shall be construed and applied consistently in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles in the United States applicable to private enterprises, as such standards may be amended, restated or replaced from time to time ("GAAP"). Article 2 TERM 2.1 Effective Date This Agreement will commence on the Effective Date and remain in full force and effect following the Effective Date until the (a) the mutual agreement of the Owners to terminate this Agreement, or (b) any other termination of this Agreement as provided hereunder. Article 3 SHARED FACILITIES 3.1 Grant of Lease in Shared Facilities (a) Effective upon the Effective Date, upon and subject to the terms, conditions, restrictions and reservations set forth in this Agreement, MA hereby leases to EGP a leasehold interest, based on a prorated division of assets by Capacity Interest, proportionate to the total Capacity Interest of the asset ownership, to those MA Shared Facilities in respect of which EGP is listed as Lessee in Exhibit A hereto, as is, with all faults and without any representations or warranties whatsoever, either express or implied, and specifically excluding any warranty of title, merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or any other warranty arising under statutory or common law, while at the same time reserving to itself 100% ownership interest in and to such Shared Facilities. (b) Within 30 days after the Effective Date, the Parties shall deliver any other notices, instruments, documents, agreements or consents as are reasonably necessary in connection with the Lease Interest in respect of the Shared Facilities. 3.2 Access to Shared Facilities Each of Lessor and Lessee and their respective Representatives shall have access to the Shared Facilities (a) for inspection of the Shared Facilities, (b) for any required maintenance and repairs of the Shared Facilities and (c) in connection with the operation of the Shared Facilities, all in accordance with this Agreement. Except in the event of an Emergency, each of Lessor and Lessee shall provide no less than seven (7) Business Days prior notice to the other prior to performing any maintenance or repairs pursuant to clause (b) above. Upon receipt of notice that one Party desires to perform maintenance and repairs on the Shared Facilities, the Parties shall immediately discuss the proposed scope of work and work in good faith to schedule the work at a time and in a manner most appropriate to both Parties. If one Party should fail to respond to the notice within five (5) Business Days of receipt, the notified Party shall reimburse the other Owner for any lost production and revenue incurred by Owner after such five (5) Business Day period in accordance with Section 6.7. Each of Lessor and Lessee and any of their respective Representatives shall: (i) follow all applicable safety, security and site rules established by MA; and (ii) comply with all applicable real estate restrictions, the Ground Lease, applicable Law and Governmental Approvals when on the premises or accessing the Shared Facilities, except to the extent that following any such rule would violate applicable Law. In the event of an Emergency, prior notice is not required to access the Shared Facilities to respond to the Emergency, but Lessor or Lessee (as applicable) shall provide notice of access to and coordinate the other as soon as reasonably practicable thereafter. 3.3 No Interference, Cooperation; Quiet Enjoyment and Over-Burdening Each Owner's use of the Shared Facilities or the operation of its Project shall not interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Owners of their respective rights in such Shared Facilities or the operation of their Projects, except as specifically provided herein. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, each Owner hereby consents to the development and operation of the Projects, and each Owner shall cooperate in good faith to accommodate the use of the Shared Facilities for the benefit of the Projects as contemplated by this Agreement. No Owner will use or permit the use of the Shared Facilities in any manner that would create waste or nuisance, or that would jeopardize the issuance or maintenance of any insurance policy relating to the Shared Facilities or any Governmental Approval as to the Shared Facilities or any Project, nor otherwise conduct or permit to be conducted operations on its Project Site which would have similar effects on, or otherwise damage or interfere with, the Shared Facilities. Article 4 SHARED EXPENSES 4.1 Liabilities for the Account of Owner Except as specifically set forth in this Agreement, each Owner shall be solely responsible for all Liabilities relating to its Project and Project Specific Assets, including all Liabilities arising from acquiring, designing, installing, constructing, using, operating, maintaining and repairing its Project Specific Assets. Each Owner shall, at its sole cost and expense, maintain or cause to be maintained in good working order and repair at all times each part of its Project that connects with or which affects the Shared Facilities. All necessary repairs to the access road shall be split evenly between each Owner. Further, each Owner shall be responsible for all Liabilities arising from such Party's actions or inactions in violation of this Agreement. 4.2 Shared Expenses; Each of Lessor and Lessee shall be responsible for and shall make payment for Shared Expenses in proportion to its Percentage Interest in respect of the relevant Shared Facility. All undisputed invoices for amounts due and owing under this Agreement shall be paid within thirty (30) days of receipt. Late payments shall accrue interest at the Default Rate. Article 5 USE OF SHARED FACILITIES 5.1 Use Subject to the other requirements of this Agreement, each Owner shall have the right to use its Ownership Interest and Lease Interest, respectively, to effectuate interconnection service for its respective Project. No Owner shall have the right, at any time and from time to time, to allocate, share or otherwise permit the use by any other Person or project of all or any portion of such Party's rights to use the Shared Facilities, unless required to do so by applicable Law. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary, the foregoing use rights include use of the capacity of electric transmission lines, transformers, substations, and other electrical components to transmit electricity from such Owner's Project in an amount that may not exceed such Owner's Capacity Interest of such capacity. 5.2 Shared Facilities Representatives Each Owner may, by written notice to the other Parties, designate an individual (the "Shared Facilities Representative"), who will have authority to bind the Owner in all matters concerning this Agreement (other than to amend this Agreement), to communicate with the other Parties, if applicable, regarding issues relating to this Agreement, including operational and maintenance issues. Each Owner may change its Shared Facilities Representative at any time and from time to time by prior written notice to the other Parties. 5.3 Liens No Owner shall create, permit or suffer to exist by, through or under their respective Representatives, and hereby waives for itself and its Representatives, any Liens on the Shared Facilities, its Ownership Interest or Lease Interest, as applicable, or on Project Specific Assets of any other Owner, in each case, other than Permitted Liens. Each Owner shall take prompt steps to discharge any Lien (other than a Permitted Lien) filed against any Shared Facility, its Ownership Interest or Lease Interest, as applicable, or Project Specific Assets of any other Owner. If an Owner is responsible for the imposition of a Lien (other than a Permitted Lien) and fails to discharge promptly any such Lien, the Owner affected by such Lien, in addition to any other rights it may have at law or equity for a breach of this Agreement, shall have the right to notify the responsible Party in writing and to take any reasonable action to satisfy, defend, settle or otherwise remove the Lien at the responsible Party's expense. Article 6 OBLIGATIONS AND CERTAIN RIGHTS OF LESSOR AND LESSEE 6.1 Standards of Performance Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement to the contrary, each Owner will operate and/or maintain, or cause to be maintained, its Project, use the Shared Facilities, and perform its obligations under this Agreement, in each case in all material respects, in accordance with (a) all applicable Laws, (b) Prudent Industry Practices, (c) any and all Governmental Approvals. Except as provided herein, no Owner will take any action, omit to take any action, or fail to perform any obligation under this Agreement, or any Governmental Approvals, as applicable, that materially and adversely affects any other Owner or other Owner's Project or gives rise to a Liability affecting any other Owner, other Owner's Project, or the Shared Facilities, including any action, omission or failure to perform an obligation that results in damage to, disconnection of, or an outage of any other Owner's Project. 6.2 Taxes On and after the Effective Date, each Party shall pay all taxes levied against the Shared Facilities before delinquency and before any fine or interest or penalty will become due or be imposed for their non-payment in accordance with Section 4.2(a). Each Owner acknowledges that it shall be liable for its own taxes with respect to the Shared Facilities or any Project Specific Assets. 6.3 No Dedication of Property; No Public Access Each Party agrees that entering into this Agreement, performing its obligations hereunder, or exercising its rights hereunder, either in whole or part, is not intended to be, and shall in no way be construed as or deemed to be a dedication to public or quasi-public use or purpose of any of the Project Specific Assets of the Party, the Project Specific Assets of another Party, any Shared Facilities, or any portion of the foregoing. Lessor and Lessee shall undertake to cooperate in enforcing such requirement for limiting physical access to the Shared Facilities. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Parties shall comply with requirements set forth in any Governmental Approvals. 6.4 Co-Location Rights Each Owner shall be permitted to encroach upon the Shared Facilities with its Project Specific Assets (including collection lines) solely to the extent necessary to develop, construct, operate and/or maintain its respective Project, provided that any such encroachments or overhang shall be subject to the noninterference protections of Section 3.3 above. In particular, Lessor's or Lessee's exercise of rights under this Section shall only be permitted in accordance with Prudent Industry Practices, and shall not interfere with or endanger the construction, operation, or maintenance of the transmission lines, substations, or operations and maintenance facilities components of the Shared Facilities. In the event of a conflict in the location or operation of the Shared Facilities and any Project Specific Assets, the Shared Facilities shall take priority over the Project Specific Assets. 6.5 Cooperation in Financing Upon reasonable request of an Owner, the other Owners shall cooperate in the financing, sale, or refinancing of such requesting Owner or Owner's Project, including the execution of estoppels, consents for the benefit of the financing parties and other similar agreements as may be reasonably requested by the requesting Owner and its financing parties, in the making of any filings required by such requesting Owner for regulatory compliance or obtaining Governmental Approvals, and in the operation and maintenance of such requesting Owner's Project, all solely at the expense of the requesting Owner. 6.6 Outage, Curtailment or Disconnection To the extent an Owner's operating Project is disconnected, incurs any downtime, is curtailed or an outage occurs, in each case, resulting in a loss of production and revenue to such Project, and the loss directly arises from another Owner's actions or inactions, then, in any such case, the responsible Owner shall reimburse the other Owner for such lost production and revenue within thirty (30) days of notice and supporting documentation of the loss. (a) Subject to the provisions of Section 6.8, any interruption, reduction in deliveries of, or other curtailment of electrical power through the Shared Facilities, in each case caused by the actions or inactions of one Owner shall be allocated as follows: first, and to the fullest extent possible, to the Owner that caused such interruption, reduction, or curtailment; and, second, to the other Owner in accordance with their Capacity Interest. 6.7 Withdrawal by Lessor or Lessee (a) At its election in its sole discretion, an Owner may cease to participate in the use of the Shared Facilities under this Agreement by delivery of a written notice (a "Withdrawal Notice") to the other Parties in which the withdrawing Owner certifies, as of the date specified in the Withdrawal Notice (a "Withdrawal Date") (i) in connection with the grant, sale, transfer, assignment and conveyance of the totality of the Ownership Interest in the Shared Facilities to Lessee if the withdrawing Party is Lessor and (ii) in connection with the termination of the Lease Interest in the Shared Facilities if the withdrawing Party is Lessee, in each case as contemplated in Section (b). The withdrawing Owner shall provide at least thirty (30) days advance written notice to the other Parties of its intention to no longer participate in the use of the Shared Facilities under this Agreement. (b) Effective upon the Withdrawal Date and upon and subject to the terms, conditions, restrictions and reservations set forth in this Agreement, the withdrawing Owner shall be deemed to have: (i) in respect of any Shared Facilities for which the withdrawing Owner is Lessor, transferred to Lessee its Ownership Interest in and to such Shared Facilities (provided that if the Lessee consists of more than one Owner, such Owners shall determine which of them shall purchase the Ownership Interest), as is, with all faults and without any representations or warranties whatsoever, either express or implied, and specifically excluding any warranty of title, merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or any other warranty arising under statutory or common law; and (ii) in respect of any Shared Facilities for which the withdrawing Party is Lessee, terminated the withdrawing Party's Lease Interest with respect to such Shared Facilities, in each case without additional compensation. (c) Effective upon the Withdrawal Date, subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, the Owner for which the Withdrawal Date applies shall release, assign or terminate its rights in the Shared Facilities, as may be requested by the other Owner in writing. (d) After its Withdrawal Date, the Owner for which the Withdrawal Notice applies shall remain a party to this Agreement but shall have no rights or obligations under this Agreement except those set forth in Section 4.1, Section 4.2 (in each case, relating to the payment of its Percentage Interest (prior to the Withdrawal Date) of Shared Expenses incurred prior to the Withdrawal Date and Removal Costs, Section 5.4, Article 9 and Article 11. 6.8 Metering Protocol RTAC (a) Until such time as the RTAC set forth below in 6.8(b) is installed, the Parties agree to follow a metering protocol ensuring the accurate recordation and allocation of output between the Projects and otherwise giving effect to each of MA's and EPG's rights and obligations in using the Shared Facilities under this Agreement to be provided by EGP within thirty (30) days of the Effective Date (the "Metering Protocol"). (i) The total output of the combined EGP Project and the MA Project is measured at the VELCO meter (VM). (ii) The total output of EGP Project is measured in the (2) VEC Meters (EGP 1&2) located at the point of interconnection for the EGP Project. (iii) The three above meters (VELCO) and the 2 EGP POI Meters collectively defined as the "Meters" (iv) The total output of the MA Plant is equal to VM-(EGP 1 + EGP 2) = MA Output. (b) Within one (1) month, EGP shall purchase, install and maintain a remote RTAC sharing these costs 50/50 as a Shared Facility with MA, to accurately record the output of both Projects. This RTAC shall be capable of recording all data available in the Meters, and create readily available access to this data for both EGP and MA as two distinct interfaces. MA shall cooperate and allow all reasonable access to any Project Specific Assets and Shared Facilities that EGP needs to facilitate such installation. Casco Systems to Submit point lists to EGPNA and MA for review and approval. Casco Systems to Ensure the RTAC will not pass unauthorized traffic between EGPNA and MA without review and approval. Casco System to Install and wire the RTAC into the Solar RIO panel and wire the RTAC to the MA Hydro switch. (c) Until such time as Central Rivers Power US, LLC installs their own dedicated internet line, the EGP internet line will be considered a Shared Facility. Following the installation of their own internet line, MA shall disconnect the LAN interface from the EGP Firewall Hydro and connect the LAN interface of the RTAC into the CRP Firewall. (d) EGP and MA share the physical fiber and conduit pathway in the ground that goes between the Hydro Main building and the Mill Control building. EGP and MA agree to share any future maintenance/repair costs 50/50. Article 12 EVENTS OF DEFAULT, TERMINATION, REMEDIES, LIMITATION OF LIABILITY, SURVIVAL 12.1 Events of Default The occurrence and continuation of any of the following events at any time during the term of this Agreement, except to the extent caused by, or resulting from, an act or omission of another Party in breach of this Agreement or an event of Force Majeure, will constitute an event of default (an "Event of Default"): (a) Payment. On and after the Effective Date, an Owner fails to pay when due any amounts required to be paid by such Owner under this Agreement and such failure to pay is not cured within fifteen Business Days following written notice from the other Owner specifying the amount to be paid; provided, however, that such period will be extended for so long as the allegedly defaulting Party is disputing in good faith such amount pursuant to the procedures set forth in Article 13. (b) Other Defaults. An Owner fails to cure any other failure to perform a material obligation under this Agreement within thirty (30) days following written notice from another Owner specifying the nature of the failure to perform, provided that if the default is not reasonably capable of being cured within thirty (30) days, then the default will be deemed cured if the defaulting Owner commences, diligently pursues, and completes action that remedies the default within ninety (90) days of receipt of such notice. (c) Interconnection Agreement. An Owner breaches, or causes the breach of, its applicable interconnection agreement, and the exercise of any remedies for such breach would have a material adverse effect on any of the Shared Facilities, this Agreement, or a non-defaulting Owner's Project, and such defaulting Owner fails to cure such breach within the time permitted by such agreement. (d) Bankruptcy. If an Owner is adjudicated as bankrupt, becomes insolvent, enters into an arrangement or composition with the Owner's creditors, suffers permanent or temporary court-appointed receivership of substantially all of such Owner's property, makes a general assignment for the benefit of creditors, or files a voluntary bankruptcy petition. 12.2 Remedies Upon the occurrence and during the continuation of an Event of Default, the other Owner will have any and all of the following remedies, exercisable only after due inquiry that an Event of Default has occurred and is continuing: (a) Tender Performance. In its sole and absolute discretion, any Owner may cure the default of the defaulting Owner by making or tendering the required payment or performance and permitting the defaulting Owner's Project to remain connected to the Shared Facilities and sales of electricity by the defaulting Owner to be continued. (b) Specific Performance. The Parties agree that damages may be an inadequate remedy for an Event of Default under this Agreement, and that each Owner will be entitled to seek injunctive and other equitable relief (including specific performance) against any other Owner to prevent or eliminate such default. (c) Other Rights and Remedies. To exercise any and all other rights and remedies which the non-defaulting Owners might otherwise have under this Agreement, at law or in equity. 12.3 Reimbursement of Expenses to Cure; Lien If an Owner elects to cure an Event of Default of another Owner, the defaulting Owner will reimburse the curing Owner for its expenses incurred in rendering the cure, plus interest at the Default Rate. The Owner curing the default will have a lien on the defaulting Owner's Ownership Interest (if the defaulting Owner is Lessor) or Lease Interest (if the defaulting Owner is Lessee), to the extent of the amount expended by the curing Owner in remedying the default (including attorneys' fees), and the defaulting Owner hereby appoints the curing Owner as its attorney-in-fact to file, record and otherwise assert such lien, to the extent of the expenditures in relation to such cure or remedy. 12.4 Remedies Cumulative No right, remedy or election given by any term of this Agreement will be deemed exclusive but each will be cumulative with all other rights, remedies and elections available under this Agreement, at law or in equity. 12.5 Waiver of Partition The Owners will not have and hereby waive the right to partition all or any portion of the Shared Facilities, or to make application to any court or authority or to commence or prosecute any action or proceeding for partition of the Shared Facilities. Each Owner will be entitled to a decree or order restraining or enjoining such partition, application, action or proceeding upon any breach of the provisions of this section 12.5. The Owners acknowledge and agree that they have been paid full consideration for the waiver provided in this Section 12.5. 12.6 Limitation of Liability Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement to the contrary, in no event, whether as a result of breach of contract, tort liability (including negligence or strict liability), or otherwise, will any Party be liable to any other Party for special, indirect, punitive or consequential damages of any nature whatsoever, including claims of customers, cost of money, loss of profit, loss of use of capital or revenue, except to the extent such damages are due under Article 9 or Section 6.7 above.
